{
  "_doc": "Archaeological Succession Track (rules §33-35). Each turn a player's marker advances one space, but may not enter a new epoch unless that epoch's entry requirements are met (§33.2); a player short of the required cities is frozen (§33.3); a player ending a turn with no cities slides back one space (§33.4, except in Stone Age). The game ends when a marker reaches the finish square or the time limit (§34).",
