    "_doc": "Read from the board AST band (map-ast.svg): 16 numbered spaces worth 100 points each (Victory Points 100..1600), plus the START arrow (space 0) and the FINISH square (space 16 = 1600). The epoch shading is a SINGLE layout shared by every nation's marker lane — nations advance along the same track at different RATES (meeting the uniform entry requirements at different times), so the track is not per-nation. `epochStart` is the first space of each epoch; boundaries read from the band are approximate (the START arrow art is oversized) but the entry requirements below are exact.",
